\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Purpose\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 We are standardizing art names to help streamline how art is associated with titles across deliveries, libraries, and internal workflows.\
A consistent naming structure makes it easier to:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 match art to the correct title quickly\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 review and organize assets with less manual sorting\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 reduce renaming during handoff\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 improve consistency across teams and vendors\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The goal is simple: cleaner file names, faster association, and fewer avoidable fixes later.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

